revision.text:
The '''Law for Temporary Measures concerning University Management''' (大学の運営に関する臨時措置法, ''Daigaku no Un'ei ni Kansuru Rinjisochihō'') of [[Japan]] was passed as Law No. 70 on August 7, 1969. It specified urgent measures to normalize management of [[universities]] disrupted by [[student activism]]. The law was repealed in 2001.{{citation needed|date=May 2013}}

