{{unreferenced|date=November 2017}} {{Infobox Government agency |agency_name = Ministry of Science and Higher Education |nativename = <small>Ministerstwo Nauki i Szkolnictwa Wyższego</small> |logo = Logo Ministerstwa Nauki i Szkolnictwa Wyższego.svg |logo_width = 200px |logo_caption = Ministerial logotype |seal = Polish Governmental and Diplomatic Plaque.svg |seal_width = 150px |seal_caption = Official governmental wall plaque |formed =2006 |preceding1 = |preceding2 = |jurisdiction = |headquarters = ul. Wspólna 1/3, [[Warsaw]] |employees = |budget = |chief1_name = [[Jarosław Gowin]] |chief1_position = Minister of Science and Higher Education |chief2_name = |chief2_position = First Deputy Minister |parent_agency = [[Council of Ministers of the Republic of Poland|Council of Ministers]] |website = [http://www.mnisw.gov.pl/ www.mnisw.gov.pl] |footnotes = }}
The '''Ministry of Science and Higher Education''' ({{lang-pl|Ministerstwo Nauki i Szkolnictwa Wyższego}}) in [[Poland]] was opened on 5 May 2006 by the Minister of Science and Higher Education, in replacement of several parts of the Ministry of Education and Science. The Minister of Science and Higher Education administers governmental activities in [[science]] and [[higher education]] and has a budget for scientific [[research]] provided by State funds. The [[Rada Nauki]] (Science Council) acts together with the Minister, in replacement of the [[Komitet Badań Naukowych]] (Science Research Council) which was closed in 2005. The headquarters of the ministry are located at ulica Wspólna 1/3, [[Warsaw]].
The current Minister of Science and Higher Education is [[Jarosław Gowin]].
== List of ministers == ===Ministers of Education and Science=== * [[Michał Seweryński]] ([[Law and Justice|PiS]]) 31 October 2005 - 5 May 2006 ===Ministers of Science and Higher Education=== * [[Michał Seweryński]], 5 May 2006 – 7 September 2007 *[[Jarosław Kaczyński]], 7 September 2007 – 11 September 2007 * [[Michał Seweryński]], 11 September 2007 – 16 November 2007 * [[Barbara Kudrycka]], 16 November 2007 – 27 November 2013 * [[Lena Kolarska-Bobińska]]<ref name="bobińska mnisw">{{cite web|title=Lena Kolarska-Bobińska|url=http://www.nauka.gov.pl/sylwetki/lena-kolarska-bobinska.html|agency=Ministerstwo Nauki i Szkolnictwa Wyższego|accessdate=2014-05-31|language=pl}}</ref>, 27 November 2013<ref name="Kolarska-Bobińska nowym ministrem">{{cite web|title=Prof. Lena Kolarska-Bobińska nowym ministrem nauki i szkolnictwa wyższego|url=http://www.nauka.gov.pl/aktualnosci-ministerstwo/prof-lena-kolarska-bobinska-nowym-ministrem-nauki-i-szkolnictwa-wyzszego.html|agency=Ministerstwo Nauki i Szkolnictwa Wyższego|date=3 grudnia 2013|accessdate=2014-05-31|language=pl}}</ref> – 15 November 2015 * [[Jarosław Gowin]], 16 November 2015
