{{Infobox video game | collapsible = | state = | italic title = | title = Powerhouse | image = | alt = | caption = | developer = [[Impressions Games|Impressions]] | publisher = [[Impressions Games|Impressions]] | series = | engine = | platforms = [[personal computer|PC]] | released = | genre = | modes = }}
'''''Powerhouse''''' is a video game developed and published by [[Impressions Games|Impressions]] for the [[personal computer|PC]].
==Gameplay== ''Powerhouse'' is a simulation in which the player is the head of a power utility, and has got to develop an electrical infrastructure for a given region before competitors can.<ref name="NG"/>
==Reception== ''[[Next Generation (magazine)|Next Generation]]'' reviewed the PC version of the game, rating it four stars out of five, and stated that "Looking at the mind-boggling array of charts and graphs in the game will provide some answers, but when all is said and done, making those decisions is up to you, and that's where the real fun in this economic simulation lies."<ref name="NG">{{cite magazine|last=|first=|title=Finals|magazine=[[Next Generation (magazine)|Next Generation]]|issue=10|publisher=[[Future US|Imagine Media]]|date=October 1995|page=119}}</ref>
